README - NayePankh NGO Management Portal
=========================================

Installation Steps:
1. Clone the repository:
   git clone https://github.com/ramnath23112005/NayePankhFullStack.git
2. Navigate to the project directory:
   cd "full Stack"
3. Install all dependencies (root, server, client):
   npm run install-all
   (Alternatively: npm install && cd server && npm install && cd ../client && npm install)
4. Set up environment variables:
   - Copy server/.env.example to server/.env (or use the provided .env)
   - Required: MONGODB_URI, JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRE, EMAIL_HOST, EMAIL_PORT,
     EMAIL_USER, EMAIL_PASS, FRONTEND_URL
5. Ensure MongoDB is running (local or Atlas cluster)

How to Run the Project:
1. Start both server and client together:
   npm run dev
2. Or start them separately:
   - Server: npm run server (runs on http://localhost:5000)
   - Client: npm run client (runs on http://localhost:3000)
3. Open browser at http://localhost:3000
4. Register a new account or login with existing credentials
5. For admin access, update user role in the database

Project Structure:
full Stack/
|-- package.json                     # Root orchestrator
|-- render.yaml                      # Render deployment config
|-- client/                          # React Frontend
|   |-- public/
|   |   |-- index.html
|   |-- src/
|   |   |-- App.js                   # Router + layouts + auth guards
|   |   |-- index.js                 # React entry
|   |   |-- context/
|   |   |   |-- AuthContext.js       # Auth state management
|   |   |   |-- ThemeContext.js      # Dark mode toggle
|   |   |-- components/
|   |   |   |-- common/              # Loader, StatCard, Skeleton
|   |   |   |-- layout/             # Navbar, Footer, Sidebar, DashboardLayout
|   |   |   |-- chat/               # ChatBot widget
|   |   |-- pages/
|   |       |-- public/             # Home, About, Programs, Events, Contact,
|   |       |                       # Login, Register, ForgotPassword,
|   |       |                       # VolunteerRegistration, InternshipApplication
|   |       |-- volunteer/          # Dashboard, Profile, MyEvents, Certificates
|   |       |-- intern/             # Dashboard, ApplicationStatus, Tasks
|   |       |-- admin/              # Dashboard, Volunteers, Internships, Events,
|   |                               # Certificates, Analytics, Settings
|-- server/                          # Express Backend
|   |-- server.js                    # Main entry point
|   |-- config/db.js                 # MongoDB connection
|   |-- models/                      # User, Volunteer, Internship, Event,
|   |                               # Certificate, Notification, Registration
|   |-- controllers/                 # auth, volunteer, internship, event,
|   |                               # certificate, notification, analytics, chat
|   |-- routes/                      # API route definitions
|   |-- middleware/                  # auth (JWT + roles), upload, validate
|   |-- utils/                       # emailer, helpers

Usage Instructions:
1. Landing Page: Browse the public homepage with animated stats, program cards,
   and testimonials carousel
2. Register: Sign up as a Volunteer or Intern (Admins are assigned manually)
3. Volunteer Flow: Complete your profile -> Get approved by admin -> Register for
   events -> Earn certificates
4. Intern Flow: Submit internship application -> Track application status -> Receive
   tasks from admin -> Update task progress -> Get certificate on completion
5. Admin Flow: Manage volunteers (approve/reject) -> Manage internships (review,
   assign tasks) -> Create events -> Generate certificates -> View analytics
6. Chatbot: Click the floating chat icon on any public page for quick information
7. Dark Mode: Toggle theme using the sun/moon icon in the navbar
